headline: Fifth Third’s Branch Expansion Strategy Driven by Data, Digital Tools
summary: CINCINNATI, December 04, 2024--Recently Fifth Third Bank (NASDAQ: FITB) unveiled plans to expand its retail branch footprint by opening more than 200 branches over the next four years, primarily in fast-growing Southeast markets. headline: Why Fifth Third’s CIO mostly buys rather than builds tech in the race to compete against banking giants
summary: To compete, Fifth Third CIO Jude Schramm leans into partnering with software providers, favoring a "buy" versus build approach.

headline: Fifth Third’s branch expansion holds tech at the center
summary: Its patent-pending heat mapping tool will power the bank’s expansion plan to add about 200 branches by 2028, primarily in the Southeast.
